It took over a year to find a new gas tank for this car, then the modifications that needed to be done for the EFI system. Finally finished with the fuel delivery 🤩!! You ever feel like you are taking 2 steps forward and 1 step back while working on a project?🤣 Restomods can be a pain in the butt, in the end worth it. I think I'm full steam ahead now. Thanks for your help @zx14

TEX MEX MOTORS and Rust Valley Restorers. (Wish the rest of our crew was here.) Also found the BEST carrot 🥕 cake EVER at Aria, I was so impressed I had to share that 🤣. Got to see @bogisgarage as it's been a few years. Awesome She-Shed booth for women at SEMA 👏

Saturday is always MY car day. Building exhaust now. Did you know I totally suck at tig welding 🤣. To be fair, I haven't had much practice.  Since this isn't a show car anymore, mig is acceptable.  Like my welding table? 🤦‍♀️ As I'm dropping everything..

The first custom car I built was my 1962 Pontiac Bonneville "The Chief" known in the Lowrider shows 1997-2002. This car is now on its third restoration in 20+ years. Business, family and life can distract you.  I have a room full of trophies 🏆 at home from this beauty. The only thing missing is my father who always helped build and did the best body work. When I do the first fire on this engine, it is dedicated to you dad💛! Pictures are from Lowrider Magazine, Street Customs Magazine, Lowrider Magazine sweepstakes trophy from Indianapolis traditional class.
